### <a id='2.3.0-rc.1'></a> 2.3.0-rc.1

* **[Feature]** Add mutual TLS route integrity option
  * With this option enabled, Router and applications use mutual TLS to verify each other's identity. Note: this is incompatible with TCP Routing and SSH access to app containers.
  * The default non-mutual TLS option is recommended for most use cases.
* **[Feature Improvement]** Default route integrity option is now "Router uses TLS to verify application identity"
  * With this option enabled, the Router verifies the identity of the application instance backends, but the application does not verify the identity of the router.
  * This is the recommended option for most use cases
* **[Feature Improvement]** Improve description for the Frontend Idle Timeout setting
  * This setting must be tuned according to the IAAS load balancer.
  * See [the documentation](https://docs.pivotal.io/pivotalcf/2-2/customizing/frontend-idle-timeout.html) for more details.
* **[Feature Improvement]** CloudController is configured to accept TLS traffic from Router
* **[Feature Improvement]** Usage Service migration with large task count backfill is now much faster
* **[Feature Improvement]** The following system applications all use the new cflinuxfs3 stack:
  * Apps Manager, Autoscaling, NFS Broker, Usage Service
* **[Bug Fix]** Fix an issue where some BOSH metrics could stop appearing in the firehose due to idle connections being killed

* **[Bug Fix]** Fixed these known issues in beta.2:
  * NFS broker push fails on upgrades from 2.2 due to missing migration from cflinuxfs2 to cflinuxfs3

* **[Known Issue]** Added known issues in rc.1:
  * Autoscaling intermittently fails with "Internal Server Error" during smoke tests

